	    <% if is_welcome == true %>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 20px 30px 10px 30px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; color: #555555;">
                <p style="margin: 0; padding-top: 10px;">Dear <%= first_name %> <%= last_name %>,</p>		
                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 15px;">Welcome to the Publication Management System. As Berkeley Lab staff, your research here is covered by the US Department of Energy’s <a href="https://www.energy.gov/sites/prod/files/2014/08/f18/DOE_Public_Access%20Plan_FINAL.pdf">public access plan</a>, which requires you to make scholarly articles you author while employed at UC freely available in <a href="https://escholarship.org">eScholarship</a>, UC's open access repository and publishing platform.</p>                
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 0px 30px 10px 30px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; color: #555555;">
                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 15px;">The Publication Management System facilitates participation in UC’s Open Access Policies. It searches multiple databases to automatically locate publications you may have authored and sends you periodic email alerts requesting that you review those items and upload manuscripts for display in eScholarship for those publications that are covered by the policy.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
