              <td style="padding: 0px 30px 20px 30px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; color: #555555;">
                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 15px;">To maintain compliance with DOE policy, the Berkeley Lab Publication Management System has identified the following actions that require your attention. Please note that only publications resulting from your research here at LBNL are covered by the policy. If you have questions about what is and is not covered, see the resources available at <a href="https://publications.sender.org">publications.sender.org</a>, or contact publications@sender.org</a>.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
	    <% else %>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 20px 30px 20px 30px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; color: #555555;">
                <p style="margin: 0; padding-top: 10px;">Dear <%= first_name %> <%= last_name %>,</p>                
                <!-- Special Paragraph: BEGIN-->
                <% if not_participating == 'yes' %>
                	<p style="margin: 0; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid red;">Our logs indicate that neither you nor your publication coordinator (or delegates) have yet to log into the publication management system to manage the published works credited to your name. Please note that compliance with the Berkeley Lab's open access policy is mandatory for all University of California faculty and staff, and lack of compliance may impact future funding for your work and that of your colleagues, as well as the Berkeley Lab's performance under its DOE contract.<br><br>If you are not a researcher and do not publish, you can have your publication management account disabled by emailing <a href="mailto:publications@sender.org">publications@sender.org</a>.</p>
                <% end %>
                <!-- Joint Appointee Paragraph: BEGIN-->
                <% if group =~ /\-lbl\-senate/ %>
                	<p style="margin: 5px 0 0 0; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid blue;">Note that because you are a Faculty Appointee, you can only log in by clicking on the <%= group.gsub(/\-lbl\-senate/, '').upcase %> button and entering your <%= group.gsub(/\-lbl\-senate/, '').upcase %> credentials (not your Berkeley Lab ones).</p>
                <% end %>
                <!-- Joint Appointee Paragraph: END-->
                <!-- Special Paragraph: END-->

                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 15px;">To maintain compliance with DOE policy, the Berkeley Lab Publication Management System has identified the following actions that require your attention. Please note that only publications resulting from your research here at LBNL are covered by the policy. If you have questions about what is and is not covered, see the resources available at <a href="https://publications.sender.org">publications.sender.org</a>, or contact publications@sender.org</a>.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>

	    <% end %>
